0. To be able to compile, you will need Gradle. If you do not wish to compile (and just use the given runnable jars) skip these steps and import the Source/orbit project in the usual way.\
1. In the menubar under Help -> Install new software\
2. Enter in the "Work with" field:  http://dist.springsource.com/release/TOOLS/gradle\
3. Select All, click next, next, etc finish.\
4. In the project manager, right-click, Import - Gradle. Click next. Select the "orbit" folder in the Source folder and then click **Build Model**. Select the all the projects.  Next next etc. \
5. Now there are two projects, core and desktop. To run the client, run Orbit.java as a java application in the desktop project (this is the client launcher)\
6. In the core project, run Server.java as a Java application (this is the server)\
